The paper deals with the problem of location estimation in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. However, based on the abstract and the keywords, it is most likely that the paper belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories, as it deals with the Cramer-Rao bound and the performance analysis of sensor networks. Other possible categories include Networked Systems (cs.NI), Machine Learning (cs.MA), and Signal Processing (cs.SI), as these areas are also relevant to the problem of location estimation in sensor networks.
